
SDWrap - a Zeroconf service discovery wrapper using wxServDisc
''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''

Quite simple wrapper app to execute some command with Zeroconf supplied
addresses and ports. Uses wxWidgets and wxServDisc for service discovery.


directory layout:

    src/wxServDisc: Zeroconf module
    src/gui:        well, the gui (made with wxglade)
   
    

prerequisites:

    wxWidgets 2.8
    
    

building:

   ./configure && make 
   

       OR (when building for Win32 with mingw):

   ./configure --build=<your build target name> --host=i586-mingw32msvc \
               --with-wx-config=<your win32 wx-config>  && make


       OR (when building under OS X):
       
   ./configure && make && make appbundle

